content:
OmniStudio for Vlocity is a set of services, components, and data model objects for creating guided interactions using your Salesforce data, and external sources.

OmniStudio for Vlocity includes:

* OmniScripts, which contain the interaction logic.
* FlexCards, which group the user interaction and data tools.
* Omnistudio Data Mappers, which transfer data between OmniStudio and Salesforce.
* Integration Procedures, which bundle server-side operations for efficiency and reuse.
* OmniOut, to run Lightning Web Components OmniScripts and FlexCards off-platform on third-party websites.

OmniStudio for Vlocity also includes:

* Calculation procedures and matrices, to automate creating quotes, and guide a customer or agent through a series of questions, pull data from various sources, and present customized quotes or eligibility determinations.
* Tracking service and OmniAnalytics, to track user interaction and performance data for OmniStudio components and events.

Differences Between OmniStudio and OmniStudio for Vlocity
OmniStudio for Vlocity uses the custom objects model, while OmniStudio uses the standard objects model. This results in some features available in one not being available in the other.

OmniStudio for Vlocity includes:

* sObject Descriptions
* Naming Conventions
* Basics
* User Interaction Tools
* Data Tools
* Lightning App and Community Builder Components Reference
title: OmniStudio for Vlocity Overview
